If you use logback, you can rid it off if you have `logback.xml` file with with root level info or reactor.util.Loggers level info. For example
```
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
&lt;configuration&gt;
    &lt;root level=&quot;info&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/configuration&gt;
```

It must be `logback.xml` not `logback-spring.xml`, because the latter is ignored  when reactor logs own state before Spring context has started

